# Next.js App Router Standards

- Keep route files in `app/` and colocate route-specific UI with the route when possible.
- Prefer server components by default; only use client components when interactivity is required.
- Keep shared UI in `components/` with clear, reusable props.
- Avoid large monolithic page files; extract repeated sections into components.
- Maintain consistent naming, semantic HTML, and accessible defaults.
- After substantive edits, run project lint/type checks before finalizing.
